TAg and also at the 3' end of VP2/3 in the structural genes, whereas infrequent recombination was present within the LTAg gene. These findings indicate that recombination within the LTAg gene has been negatively selected against during polyomaviral evolution and support the recent proposal for taxonomic classification based on LTAg to define novel PyV species.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Carr, M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Gonzalez, G.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sasaki, M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ito, K.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Ishii, A.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Hang'ombe, B. M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Mweene, A. S.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Orba, Y.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Sawa, H.", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["*Recombination, Genetic", "Animals", "Antigens, Viral, Tumor/*genetics", "Chiroptera/*virology", "Cluster Analysis", "Genome, Viral", "LTAg", "Phylogeny", "Polyomavirus Infections/*veterinary/virology", "Polyomavirus/*classification/genetics/*isolation & purification", "Sequence Analysis, DNA", "Sequence Homology", "Zambia", "bat", "hot spot", "polyomavirus", "recombination", "Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/ab59a1dd06e2e6401503cb6cc6a529a9", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/8a228e75d4d6f8219e862161589bba491e36e246b39a6e9b8c1385b56795ba93", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/BUSJBSBX", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/BUSJBSBX", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/2fe7821dfebc82a584010962b2011231!/b134253-136535", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/ce1e7618f237ff56e74d51f496e811a3", "rel